wrapScienceJ.metaData.container

Class MetaData

  • java.lang.Object
    • wrapScienceJ.metaData.container.MetaDataContainer
      • wrapScienceJ.metaData.container.MetaData
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MetaDataRetriever

    public class MetaData
extends MetaDataContainer
    This class is intended to contain metadata information regarding an image. THis metadata can be configured on a directory by directory basis and read from a configuration file in that directory.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MetaData

        public MetaData(java.lang.String title)
        Allows to construct a config for a generic process with an empty collection of attribute data. The config file name takes a default value starting with "default__" .
        Parameters:
        title - The short human readable title, used as a postfix in conf files (e.g. for use as dialog box title) The attribute list initially contains a StringNoAttrib with short description keyShortDescriptionForTitle and as value the title (e.g. to display in a dialog box); as well as a StringNoAttrib with short description "configFileNameDoNotUse" and as value the configFileName, to retrieve the configuration file if possible.

      • MetaData

        public MetaData(java.lang.String title,
                java.lang.String configFileName)
        Allows to construct a config for a generic process with an empty collection of attribute data
        Parameters:
        title - The short human readable title, used as a postfix in conf files (e.g. for use as dialog box title)
        configFileName - The configuration file to be placed in a given directory The attribute list initially contains a StringNoAttrib with short description keyShortDescriptionForTitle and as value the title (e.g. to display in a dialog box); as well as a StringNoAttrib with short description "configFileNameDoNotUse" and as value the configFileName, to retrieve the configuration file if possible.

      • setMetaDataFileName

        public void setMetaDataFileName(java.lang.String basename)

        Parameters:
